sacrifice paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a fenced area on which a farmer will bring in silage, hay or other feed to stock in very wet weather , causing the sward to be pugged and trampled.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
